d religion-with particular emphasis on gender and economic reform. Barker concludes that Mill's interpretation of liberty is not well described as either negative or positive. Instead, liberty consists in the mental independence or thinking power of the educated individuals composing and challenging majorities. CHRIS BARKER is Assistant Professor of Political Science at the American University in Cairo.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAristocracy (Political science). 0aDemocracy and education. 4aPhilosophy. 4aPolitics & Economics. 4aSocial History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aAristocracy.  aCivic Education.  aDemocracy.  aIndividual Independence.  aJ.S. Mill.  aLiberty.  aPolitical Power.  aPolitical Thinker.  aTyranny of the Majority.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311143106240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781787443709?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787443709423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787443709/original  a978-3-11-143106-2  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles